id: pm-kl19
title: "GH-548: rename and migrate workspace id_prefix without manual history-breaking rewrites"
description: "Add a governed SDK and CLI migration for changing a workspace id_prefix while preserving item filenames, parent/dependency references, history integrity, cursors, indexes, and external mapping evidence."
type: Issue
status: open
priority: 2
tags[6]: "area:history","area:schema","area:sdk",gh-issue,migration,workspace
created_at: "2026-07-13T22:19:48.147Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-13T22:19:48.147Z"
author: codex-root
estimated_minutes: 480
acceptance_criteria: "SDK exposes typed plan/apply/verify primitives and CLI is a thin adapter; dry-run lists every id and reference rewrite with collision detection; apply is locked, resumable, crash-safe, and fully audited; history verification and every parent, blocker, dependency, plan link, cursor, and derived index remain consistent; packed temp-workspace tests cover collisions, partial failure, resume, custom prefixes, closed history, and rollback guidance"
parent: pm-dijg
risk: high
confidence: medium
reporter: codex-root
severity: high
repro_steps: "Initialize and populate a workspace, change the desired id_prefix, and attempt to migrate existing ids using supported commands; no governed operation exists, leaving manual file and reference rewrites as the only path."
expected_result: "A dry-run-first SDK and CLI migration plans and applies an atomic, resumable id-prefix rewrite across items, graph references, history, indexes, runtime cursors, linked evidence, and import/export mappings with audited rollback-by-new-event semantics."
actual_result: Changing id_prefix for an established workspace requires error-prone direct tracker file edits that can break history hashes and leave stale references.
component: workspace identity schema and migration engine
customer_impact: "Long-lived or federated projects cannot safely rename their identity namespace, blocking reorganization, imports, mergers, and VCS-like workflows."
